rest_of_day_open: I'm on the cusp of a new week and I feel like there is the potential for new opportunities. I'm in a state of transition and things can go many different ways. At this point right now, I feel like there are a few things I can do with myself. The hardest part is going to be starting something a sticking to it.
critical_positive: My conversation partner had a very interesting backstory, and many things that they have to deal with on a regular basis. I found their perspective and life experience very interesting and I had a fun time getting to understand things about them. They had to deal with a chronic illness that I knew little about, so I liked the chance to hear about it from someone who lives with it every day.
critical_negative: I was worried at some points that my conversation partner might be uncomfortable with the path the conversation was taking. They mentioned that the medication they use can make them very sensitive to things for no reason, but i wanted to give them an out and change the subject if they needed to. The assured me that everything was ok, but I felt guilty about maybe pushing a subject too far.

rest_of_day_open: Over the next week, I anticipate some hard times. I am having a health issue that must be addressed very soon. I was able to talk about this with my chat partner (which was nice) and it made me feel less isolated and afraid.  I will deal with the issue one moment at a time!
critical_positive: Both me and my chat partner are in pivotal positions in our lives.  We are both looking to redirect our work lives.  I have health problems and he has a family in health care. We are both a little concerned about covid-19.  I believe he is also same-sex attracted, which we both have in common.
critical_negative: We had a little bit of time when I couldn't see his actual face on the screen. I could see a graphic that prolific or Better UPs has added to show that the video is running but i could not see his face. I could hear him and he could see my face. He said there was a storm in the area, so that might have been the issue.
